          <p class='first-para'>
            The Minister posed two questions. Is there not a third? If the person has come
            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_152gc' title='Col. 152GC &mdash; HL Deb 03 June 2003 vol 648 c152GC' name='column_152gc' href='#column_152gc' rel='bookmark'>152GC</a>
            back to this country from another country, should he be returned to that country to stand trial for something that would not be an offence if done in this country?
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0648P0-05174'>
        <a name='S5LV0648P0_20030603_GCR_70'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-david-filkin' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0648P0_20030603_GCR_70' title='Link to this speech by Mr David Filkin' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
